# reinguard bridge (Adapter layer)

This file is an **adapter**: it points at the Semantics layer (`.reinguard/`)
and Substrate (`rgd`). Do not duplicate body text from `.reinguard/` here.

## Entry points

- **Substrate config**: [.reinguard/reinguard.yaml](../../.reinguard/reinguard.yaml) ‚Äî `schema_version`, `default_branch`, `providers` (ADR-0008, ADR-0009).
- **Label SSOT**: [.reinguard/labels.yaml](../../.reinguard/labels.yaml) ‚Äî GitHub label categories and `commit_prefix` (ADR-0008).
- **Knowledge catalog**: [.reinguard/knowledge/manifest.json](../../.reinguard/knowledge/manifest.json) ‚Äî `entries[]` with `id`, `path`, `description`, `triggers`, `when` (ADR-0010).
- **Policy catalog** (normative, not in knowledge manifest): [.reinguard/policy/catalog.yaml](../../.reinguard/policy/catalog.yaml) ‚Äî `entries[]` with `id`, `path`, `description`; bodies live under [.reinguard/policy/](../../.reinguard/policy/).
- **Control catalog** (human-maintained index; not read by validate): [.reinguard/control/catalog.yaml](../../.reinguard/control/catalog.yaml) ‚Äî `entries[]` with `id`, `path`, `type`, `description`. **Rule YAML** under [.reinguard/control/states/](../../.reinguard/control/states/), [routes/](../../.reinguard/control/routes/), [guards/](../../.reinguard/control/guards/) ‚Äî consumed by `config.Load` / `rgd config validate`.

## Always-active policy

Follow these policy documents in every interaction:

- [safety--agent-invariants.md](../../.reinguard/policy/safety--agent-invariants.md) ‚Äî **HARD STOPS (HS-*)**:
  - **HS-CI-MERGE** ‚Äî green CI before merge; no `--admin`
  - **HS-PR-TEMPLATE** ‚Äî all PR template sections required
  - **HS-PR-BASE** ‚Äî PRs target `main` only
  - **HS-LOCAL-VERIFY** ‚Äî `go test` / `go vet` / `golangci-lint` before push
  - **HS-NO-SKIP** ‚Äî no skipping verification without documented exception
  - **HS-REVIEW-RESOLVE** ‚Äî disposition reply before resolving threads
  - **HS-MERGE-CONSENSUS** ‚Äî no auto-merge while review pending
- [coding--standards.md](../../.reinguard/policy/coding--standards.md) ‚Äî English artifacts, `gofmt`, `go vet`, **Change scope** (same-kind sweep), ADR/CLI authority

## Knowledge retrieval

- **Primary:** `rgd context build` ‚Äî use `knowledge.entries` in stdout JSON (each entry‚Äôs required `when` is evaluated against observation + merged `state.*` signals to filter inclusion; see `docs/cli.md`).
- **Catalog only:** triage with `entries` in `manifest.json` when you are not running `rgd` (paths and metadata; `when` shows relevance conditions).
- Read only the Markdown paths you need.
- **Optional** trigger substring filter (OR-union with observation signals): save observation JSON (`rgd observe > /tmp/rgd-observe.json`), then:

```bash
rgd knowledge pack --observation-file /tmp/rgd-observe.json --query '<keyword>'
```

`--query` matches **triggers** only (case-insensitive substring), not `description`.

## After changing knowledge front matter

Run `rgd knowledge index` and commit `manifest.json`; then `rgd config validate`.

